HEADWORD: Brant
<hw>Brant</hw> <pr>(br⟦acr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.<er>Brand
goose</er>, <er>Brent</er>, <er>Brenicle</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A species of wild goose (<spn>Branta bernicla</spn>) -- called also
<altname>brent</altname> and <altname>brand goose</altname>. The name is
also applied to other related species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

